@startuml
title MediMatch – User Sequence Diagram (Donor & Recipient Flow)
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #1E4B8E
  LifeLineBorderColor #1E4B8E
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FBFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #1E4B8E
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

actor "Donor Facility" as Donor
actor "Recipient Facility" as Recipient
participant "Frontend (UI)" as UI
participant "Backend Server" as Server
database "Database" as DB
participant "Notification Service" as Notify

== Step 1: Request & Listing ==
Donor -> UI : Create Surplus Listing
UI -> Server : Submit Listing Data
Server -> DB : Save Listing

Recipient -> UI : Submit Supply Request
UI -> Server : Send Request Data
Server -> DB : Store Request Record

== Step 2: Match & Validation ==
Server -> DB : Retrieve Listings & Requests
Server -> Server : Run Matching Algorithm
Server -> DB : Save Match Record
DB --> Server : Match Confirmed

== Step 3: Notifications ==
Server -> Notify : Notify Donor & Recipient
Notify -> Donor : "Recipient Request Found"
Notify -> Recipient : "Matching Listing Found"

== Step 4: Confirmation ==
Donor -> Server : Approve / Decline Match
Server -> DB : Update Status
Server -> Notify : Send Confirmation to Recipient

@enduml
